devrc 0.4.0
⚡ task automation tool on steroids ⚡

USAGE:
    devrc [FLAGS] [OPTIONS] [--] [TASKS OR ARGS]...

FLAGS:
        --describe      Describe task
    -d, --detailed      Show detailed tasks list
        --dry-run       Print commands and skip execution
    -g                  Force to use global .devrc file
    -h, --help          Prints help information
    -l, --list          List available tasks and their arguments
        --evariables    Show global environment variables
        --variables     Show global variables
    -q, --quiet         Suppress all output
        --stdin         Read stdin instead of reading default devrcfile
    -V, --version       Prints version information
    -v, --verbose       Enable verbose mode (-v, -vv, -vvv, etc.)

OPTIONS:
    -f, --f <CONFIG>...          Specify an alternate Devrcfile files
                                 (default: Devrcfile)
        --completions <SHELL>    Print shell completion script for <SHELL> [possible values: zsh, bash, fish,
                                 powershell, elvish]
        --set <VAR=VALUE>...     Override <VARIABLE> with <VALUE>

ARGS:
    <TASKS OR ARGS>...    

Wish you productive coding!
Visit https://github.com/devrc-hub/devrc to get more info about devrc.
